{"id": 15114, "date": "1987-03-12T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-03-12T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=15114"}, "modified": "2026-06-10T15:24:24", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-10T22:24:24", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-and-beaver-brown-do-you-want-to-dance", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/03/12/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-beaver-brown-do-you-want-to-dance/", "title": {"rendered": "Do You Want to Dance"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>The summer of 1982 looms large in Springsteen legend.</p>\n<p>The River Tour was a year in the past; the marathon Born in the U.S.A. Tour was still two years in the future. But for Bruce Springsteen, an &#8220;off-year&#8221; summer meant no less than <em>twenty\u00a0</em>unadvertised surprise appearances at Jersey shore clubs.</p>\n<p>From storied venues like The Stone Pony and Big Man&#8217;s West to the lesser-known Brighton Bar and the Monmouth County Fair, Bruce seemed to be everywhere that summer.</p>\n<p>Most often appearing with Stone Pony house band Cats on a Smooth Surface, Bruce also appeared with Clarence Clemons &amp; The Red Bank Rockers, Sonny Kenn &amp; The Wild Ideas, Billy Chinnock, The Iron City Houserockers, Mama Tried and Stray Cats.</p>\n<p>Bruce also played with Beaver Brown&#8211;still a year away from the peak of their <em>Eddie and the Cruisers </em>popularity&#8211;four times that summer, including Saturday night, August 7th.</p>\n<p>That night is best known for the debut of what would eventually become &#8220;Downbound Train,&#8221; but for my money, the highlight of the night was Bruce and the band&#8217;s first-ever performance of Bobby Freeman&#8217;s &#8220;Do You Want to Dance.&#8221; Without the demands of nightly marathon concerts, Bruce&#8217;s vocals were in great form, and their performance was captured in very good quality for an almost forty-year-old bar gig. Check it out:</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BR6wGGYOpXM?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Bobby Freeman&#8217;s Latin-rhythm 1958 original didn&#8217;t rock quite as hard as Bruce and Beaver Brown&#8217;s version, but it was popular enough to notch a #5 berth on the Billboard Hot 100 and #2 on the R&amp;B chart.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xVff7TJzc-Q?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>Fun fact: Freeman followed up &#8220;Do You Want to Dance&#8221; with a single called &#8220;Betty Lou Got a New Pair of Shoes.&#8221; By the next summer, movie audiences would be rocking out to Beaver Brown performing that song, too.</p>\n<p><strong>Do You Want to Dance<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> August 7, 1982 (Red Bank, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> October 3, 1982 (Asbury Park, NJ)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 January 6, 2020</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: Listen to Bruce Springsteen join Rhode Island rockers Beaver Brown in a joyful cover of Bobby Freeman\u2019s \u201cDo You Want to Dance\u201d in a surprise appearance in the summer of 1982.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 15348, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [4, 3617, 5], "tags": [2610, 2609, 2608], "class_list": ["post-15114", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-it-takes-two", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-bobby-freeman", "tag-do-you-wanna-dance", "tag-do-you-want-to-dance"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Bobby-Freeman-album.jpg?fit=820%2C820&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-3VM", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 13920, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/02/03/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-cats-on-a-smooth-surface-rock-baby-rock-it/", "url_meta": {"origin": 15114, "position": 0}, "title": "Rock Baby, Rock It", "author": "Ken", "date": "February 3, 1987", "format": false, "excerpt": "One time only: Bruce Springsteen joins Stone Pony house band Cats on a Smooth Surface to cover a l